Spec: Cline Validator

Platform: Node.js

Purpose:
  Validate the generated Cline skills package using documented Cline skill constraints until a stable native validator exists.

Owns:
  ./cline-validator.js

Must:
  Run without third-party dependencies or network access.
  Accept the generated plugin root path as its only command-line argument.
  Validate `skills/*/SKILL.md` directories under the given plugin root.
  Require every skill directory name to use kebab-case.
  Require each `SKILL.md` file to start with YAML frontmatter.
  Require `name` and `description` frontmatter fields.
  Require frontmatter `name` to match the skill directory name.
  Allow extra frontmatter fields used by other compatible skill consumers.
  Enforce Cline's documented `description` maximum of 1024 characters.
  Enforce Cline's documented instruction body guidance with a conservative estimate under 5000 tokens.
  Print a concise validation summary on success.
  Print concrete file-specific failures and exit nonzero on validation failure.

Must not:
  Modify generated plugin output.
  Validate Junie, Copilot, Codex, Claude, or Antigravity package-specific rules.
